1
00:01:24,930 --> 00:01:30,030
[Youthful Glory]

2
00:01:30,120 --> 00:01:32,890
[Episode 12]

3
00:01:34,009 --> 00:01:36,000
Your Highness, you've always been
mindful of your health,

4
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:37,800
careful to avoid anything you can't eat.

5
00:01:37,800 --> 00:01:38,979
Why did you still

6
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:40,130
have the fish today?

7
00:01:42,720 --> 00:01:44,210
His Highness deboned it himself,

8
00:01:44,210 --> 00:01:45,570
so attentive and considerate.

9
00:01:45,570 --> 00:01:46,810
If I didn't eat it,

10
00:01:46,850 --> 00:01:49,310
wouldn't that be
turning down his kindness?

11
00:01:49,800 --> 00:01:51,080
But I didn't eat much.

12
00:01:51,130 --> 00:01:52,860
I'll be fine in a couple of days.

13
00:01:57,970 --> 00:01:58,680
Right,

14
00:01:58,770 --> 00:01:59,930
when you organize things,

15
00:01:59,930 --> 00:02:01,160
take out everything that hasn't been used

16
00:02:01,160 --> 00:02:02,080
in recent years.

17
00:02:02,080 --> 00:02:03,520
Make the most of everything.

18
00:02:03,520 --> 00:02:05,210
Don't spend money buying

19
00:02:05,210 --> 00:02:06,680
what we have in the future.

20
00:02:09,210 --> 00:02:10,110
Yes.

21
00:02:11,560 --> 00:02:13,050
Your Highness, you'll go out tomorrow.

22
00:02:13,050 --> 00:02:14,290
Rest early.

23
00:02:14,360 --> 00:02:16,490
Let me help you wash up and get changed.

24
00:02:19,890 --> 00:02:20,490
Thank you.

25
00:02:22,480 --> 00:02:26,490
[Capital]

26
00:02:23,020 --> 00:02:23,550
Let's go.

27
00:02:27,950 --> 00:02:28,620
My lord.

28
00:02:29,150 --> 00:02:30,860
The funds, provisions, and supplies
from the Ministry of Revenue

29
00:02:30,860 --> 00:02:31,560
have all been accounted for.

30
00:02:31,560 --> 00:02:32,890
No errors or omissions.

31
00:02:33,829 --> 00:02:34,390
Good.

32
00:02:34,950 --> 00:02:36,060
Depart immediately.

33
00:02:36,060 --> 00:02:36,660
Yes.

34
00:02:42,670 --> 00:02:43,600
Father-in-law!

35
00:02:43,900 --> 00:02:44,829
Father-in-law!

36
00:02:52,390 --> 00:02:53,150
Xu.

37
00:02:55,020 --> 00:02:56,020
Why are you here?

38
00:02:56,550 --> 00:02:58,060
I heard you're leaving the capital
for a dangerous mission.

39
00:02:58,060 --> 00:02:59,190
I came to see you off.

40
00:02:59,829 --> 00:03:01,230
Tan was worried
the damp and cold of Lizhou

41
00:03:01,230 --> 00:03:03,150
might aggravate your old leg injury,

42
00:03:03,150 --> 00:03:04,990
so she prepared
the mink-lined knee warmers,

43
00:03:04,990 --> 00:03:06,990
hoping you'll take good care of yourself

44
00:03:06,990 --> 00:03:08,320
and return safely soon.

45
00:03:10,990 --> 00:03:12,400
Tan

46
00:03:13,460 --> 00:03:15,060
has always feared partings.

47
00:03:16,180 --> 00:03:17,680
When I left for Yangxi Prefecture,

48
00:03:17,680 --> 00:03:19,680
she didn't come to see me off either.

49
00:03:19,740 --> 00:03:21,620
But she gave me a cloth tiger,

50
00:03:23,180 --> 00:03:25,590
saying it could keep me company

51
00:03:26,150 --> 00:03:28,190
in her stead every day.

52
00:03:32,300 --> 00:03:33,230
Father-in-law.

53
00:03:33,920 --> 00:03:34,550
This package contains

54
00:03:34,550 --> 00:03:36,390
hemostatic and detoxifying medicine,

55
00:03:36,390 --> 00:03:38,720
and a few sets of portable hidden weapons.

56
00:03:38,829 --> 00:03:40,860
Just in case.

57
00:03:45,230 --> 00:03:46,240
Xu,

58
00:03:47,670 --> 00:03:49,130
you're truly thoughtful.

59
00:03:54,870 --> 00:03:56,200
It was Chancellor Su

60
00:03:56,230 --> 00:03:58,630
who strongly recommended you go to Lizhou.

61
00:03:59,110 --> 00:04:00,880
Since Yangxi Prefecture
is about to change hands,

62
00:04:00,880 --> 00:04:03,340
there's bound to be unrest
among the troops.

63
00:04:03,340 --> 00:04:05,690
I hope you'll be cautious and vigilant.

64
00:04:05,780 --> 00:04:07,020
Stay alert.

65
00:04:07,710 --> 00:04:10,090
Father-in-law, be careful.

66
00:04:14,790 --> 00:04:15,590
Stay.

67
00:04:17,910 --> 00:04:18,839
Let's go!

68
00:04:35,740 --> 00:04:37,150
Greetings, Your Highness.

69
00:04:37,150 --> 00:04:38,060
What's wrong?

70
00:04:38,620 --> 00:04:39,690
Your Highness,

71
00:04:39,740 --> 00:04:42,360
I came to apply ointment for Her Highness.

72
00:04:42,500 --> 00:04:44,230
Her Highness has been allergic
to river fish since childhood.

73
00:04:44,230 --> 00:04:45,790
It causes rashes every time.

74
00:04:45,790 --> 00:04:47,550
I know how much she values her appearance,

75
00:04:47,550 --> 00:04:49,550
so I want to apply ointment for her again.

76
00:04:49,550 --> 00:04:51,409
That way, she can recover faster.

77
00:04:52,300 --> 00:04:53,590
Since she knew she can't eat it,

78
00:04:53,590 --> 00:04:54,850
why didn't she refuse?

79
00:04:56,260 --> 00:04:57,790
You deboned it personally.

80
00:04:57,820 --> 00:04:59,680
Of course she'd eat it willingly.

81
00:05:07,910 --> 00:05:08,670
Give it to me.

82
00:05:54,260 --> 00:05:59,140
♪ You walk beside me
like a gentle breeze ♪

83
00:06:02,180 --> 00:06:06,890
♪ We journey through mountains,
hearts entwined ♪

84
00:06:09,240 --> 00:06:16,100
♪ As stars shift and time flows by ♪

85
00:06:11,450 --> 00:06:12,970
I look like a villain?

86
00:06:14,350 --> 00:06:15,230
Yes.

87
00:06:17,560 --> 00:06:21,460
♪ I wait for your eyes to meet mine ♪

88
00:06:24,400 --> 00:06:29,340
♪ Your name reflects
within a smiling face ♪

89
00:06:31,490 --> 00:06:36,550
♪ May we hold hands,
and not waste these fleeting years ♪

90
00:06:38,870 --> 00:06:39,740
Fool.

91
00:06:39,220 --> 00:06:46,330
♪ With trailing vines as our song,
mountains and seas stay ever bound ♪

92
00:06:40,060 --> 00:06:41,620
May Buddha grant me

93
00:06:41,620 --> 00:06:43,310
a suitable husband.

94
00:06:43,350 --> 00:06:44,740
His appearance must be handsome,

95
00:06:44,740 --> 00:06:46,680
only then would he be a match for me.

96
00:06:46,820 --> 00:06:49,030
It would be best if he

97
00:06:47,580 --> 00:06:51,820
♪ Painting a scroll of passion,
fierce and profound ♪

98
00:06:49,060 --> 00:06:50,210
is tall enough.

99
00:06:50,670 --> 00:06:51,870
If he practices martial arts,

100
00:06:51,870 --> 00:06:53,100
may it be the sword—

101
00:06:53,090 --> 00:06:57,270
♪ The vows we made together ♪

102
00:06:53,630 --> 00:06:55,670
his movements graceful and refined—

103
00:06:55,670 --> 00:06:56,740
so that

104
00:06:56,790 --> 00:06:58,200
when he wields his sword,

105
00:06:57,430 --> 00:07:01,210
♪ I'll never regret guarding you
or being wild with you ♪

106
00:06:58,230 --> 00:07:01,370
I'd accompany him with the guqin,
creating a scene of perfect harmony.

107
00:07:01,370 --> 00:07:07,200
♪ Because the landscape of fate
always bears your shadow ♪

108
00:07:08,130 --> 00:07:12,230
♪ I wish to become your birthmark ♪

109
00:07:12,380 --> 00:07:16,460
♪ Let time carve our sincerity ♪

110
00:07:16,680 --> 00:07:18,350
♪ Red threads bind us tightly ♪

111
00:07:18,580 --> 00:07:22,600
♪ This is what happiness looks like ♪

112
00:07:23,200 --> 00:07:26,210
♪ I vow again with raised hands ♪

113
00:07:24,150 --> 00:07:26,010
The fourth daughter of the Ming family,

114
00:07:26,010 --> 00:07:28,740
graceful, virtuous, smart,

115
00:07:26,770 --> 00:07:30,130
♪ Let me hear your tender thoughts ♪

116
00:07:28,740 --> 00:07:30,030
and gentle,

117
00:07:30,070 --> 00:07:33,030
is now of marriageable age.

118
00:07:30,460 --> 00:07:32,780
♪ Follow the stars in your eyes ♪

119
00:07:33,030 --> 00:07:36,580
♪ I'll never lose my way ♪

120
00:07:33,140 --> 00:07:36,340
She is hereby bestowed in marriage
to Jiang Xu, Prince of Dingbei,

121
00:07:36,130 --> 00:07:38,720
[Ming Tan] [Jiang Xu]

122
00:07:36,590 --> 00:07:38,950
and officially titled the Princess of Dingbei.

123
00:07:37,860 --> 00:07:41,490
♪ Though the winds may rise,
my hope never fades ♪

124
00:07:41,820 --> 00:07:45,750
♪ At dawn and dusk,
love has no beginning ♪

125
00:07:46,030 --> 00:07:52,460
♪ Time guides us to this vow for life ♪

126
00:07:47,870 --> 00:07:49,930
After everything that has happened,

127
00:07:50,050 --> 00:07:52,250
words still can't express my feelings.

128
00:07:52,880 --> 00:08:01,250
♪ When the mountains bloom,
I'll meet you again ♪

129
00:07:52,990 --> 00:07:53,960
Now,

130
00:07:55,350 --> 00:07:56,920
I don't know if marrying you

131
00:07:56,970 --> 00:07:58,510
was my expediency

132
00:07:59,620 --> 00:08:01,480
or if I came up with the expediency

133
00:08:02,470 --> 00:08:04,260
because I wanted to marry you.

134
00:08:25,640 --> 00:08:34,570
[Qi'an Hall]

135
00:08:29,230 --> 00:08:30,070
Go in later.

136
00:08:30,070 --> 00:08:31,540
Let her sleep a bit longer.

137
00:08:31,660 --> 00:08:32,190
Yes.

138
00:08:35,600 --> 00:08:36,659
Are there any other foods

139
00:08:36,659 --> 00:08:37,830
Tan can't eat?

140
00:08:38,309 --> 00:08:39,190
Your Highness,

141
00:08:39,230 --> 00:08:41,380
Her Highness can't eat anything smoked.

142
00:08:41,380 --> 00:08:43,470
And she doesn't like fowl or game meats.

143
00:08:43,470 --> 00:08:45,400
She can't eat anything spicy at all

144
00:08:45,660 --> 00:08:48,060
and should avoid strong-flavored spices.

145
00:08:48,660 --> 00:08:50,190
Make a list for the kitchen.

146
00:08:50,190 --> 00:08:52,130
Tell them to avoid all those.

147
00:08:52,260 --> 00:08:53,020
Yes.

148
00:08:54,100 --> 00:08:57,380
[Qi'an Hall]

149
00:09:00,600 --> 00:09:02,030
Is His Highness blaming us

150
00:09:02,030 --> 00:09:03,620
for not taking good care of Her Highness?

151
00:09:03,620 --> 00:09:04,470
Foolish one.

152
00:09:04,470 --> 00:09:05,620
He's not blaming us.

153
00:09:05,720 --> 00:09:06,930
Clearly, he just

154
00:09:06,950 --> 00:09:09,140
cares about his wife very much.

155
00:09:36,530 --> 00:09:37,550
Suxin.

156
00:09:46,250 --> 00:09:47,110
Your Highness.

157
00:09:52,230 --> 00:09:53,070
It's all gone.

158
00:09:53,900 --> 00:09:54,650
His Highness

159
00:09:54,680 --> 00:09:55,870
took care of you the whole night.

160
00:09:55,870 --> 00:09:56,810
Your Highness, that's why

161
00:09:56,810 --> 00:09:58,310
your rashes disappeared so quickly.

162
00:09:58,310 --> 00:09:59,210
Xu?

163
00:10:01,380 --> 00:10:02,500
He slept

164
00:10:02,590 --> 00:10:04,190
in the Qi'an Hall last night?

165
00:10:06,420 --> 00:10:07,900
His Highness took the ointment

166
00:10:07,900 --> 00:10:09,110
and asked me to leave.

167
00:10:09,210 --> 00:10:10,820
So he must have applied it for you

168
00:10:10,820 --> 00:10:11,700
personally.

169
00:10:17,110 --> 00:10:18,860
How come I didn't know at all?

170
00:10:19,710 --> 00:10:20,500
Your Highness,

171
00:10:20,500 --> 00:10:21,340
which outfit would you like to wear

172
00:10:21,340 --> 00:10:22,740
for today's outing?

173
00:10:23,710 --> 00:10:24,640
Right.

174
00:10:24,980 --> 00:10:26,390
I have an appointment with Minmin today

175
00:10:26,390 --> 00:10:28,390
to trial our storybook on the stage.

176
00:10:29,310 --> 00:10:30,310
What time is it?

177
00:10:30,340 --> 00:10:31,960
It's already past 9 a.m.

178
00:10:32,560 --> 00:10:33,600
9 a.m.?

179
00:10:34,420 --> 00:10:36,070
Why didn't you wake me up earlier?

180
00:10:36,070 --> 00:10:38,500
His... His Highness stopped us.

181
00:10:38,500 --> 00:10:40,630
He said he wanted you
to sleep a bit longer.

182
00:10:40,630 --> 00:10:43,110
Your Highness,
His Highness really cares about you.

183
00:10:43,110 --> 00:10:44,600
He even specially asked
about your dietary restrictions

184
00:10:44,600 --> 00:10:47,060
and ordered the kitchen
to keep them in mind.

185
00:10:52,420 --> 00:10:54,120
You talk too much.

186
00:10:55,710 --> 00:10:56,620
Help me get dressed.

187
00:10:56,620 --> 00:10:57,450
Yes.

188
00:10:57,910 --> 00:11:01,220
[Elegant Songs and Dances]

189
00:11:06,440 --> 00:11:07,780
Nowadays, in the capital,

190
00:11:07,780 --> 00:11:09,320
isn't the most popular place

191
00:11:09,320 --> 00:11:11,120
to enjoy plays Wentao Pavilion?

192
00:11:11,230 --> 00:11:13,090
Which troupe is this?

193
00:11:13,110 --> 00:11:14,310
Which performers did they invite?

194
00:11:14,310 --> 00:11:16,370
How come I've never seen them before?

195
00:11:17,420 --> 00:11:18,620
I heard they're refugees.

196
00:11:18,620 --> 00:11:19,480
Your Highness,

197
00:11:20,190 --> 00:11:21,520
will this... work?

198
00:11:23,710 --> 00:11:25,780
I can't think of a better way for now.

199
00:11:25,800 --> 00:11:27,720
Just take it one step at a time.

200
00:11:27,830 --> 00:11:29,880
But there's quite a crowd today.

201
00:11:38,280 --> 00:11:39,660
Let me remind you one more time.

202
00:11:39,660 --> 00:11:40,890
When he gets injured,

203
00:11:40,990 --> 00:11:42,270
you walk away heartlessly.

204
00:11:42,270 --> 00:11:43,500
You're not truly heartless.

205
00:11:43,500 --> 00:11:44,770
You must show the character's

206
00:11:44,770 --> 00:11:45,500
kindness

207
00:11:45,620 --> 00:11:47,710
and the subtle shift in her feelings.

208
00:11:48,110 --> 00:11:49,730
And during the upcoming fight scene,

209
00:11:49,730 --> 00:11:50,430
be careful.

210
00:11:50,450 --> 00:11:51,350
Stay well coordinated.

211
00:11:51,350 --> 00:11:52,340
Get ready.

212
00:11:54,990 --> 00:11:55,920
Everyone,

213
00:11:56,190 --> 00:11:57,620
today's new play,

214
00:11:57,660 --> 00:12:00,020
"The Tale of the Domineering Prince
and His Beloved Princess:

215
00:12:00,020 --> 00:12:01,140
Disaster Relief",

216
00:12:01,380 --> 00:12:03,240
tells the secret love story

217
00:12:03,270 --> 00:12:05,220
between a war hero prince

218
00:12:05,240 --> 00:12:06,810
and his noble princess,

219
00:12:06,830 --> 00:12:08,700
along with their disaster relief deeds.

220
00:12:08,700 --> 00:12:10,310
If you are interested,

221
00:12:10,370 --> 00:12:12,780
stay and enjoy.

222
00:12:13,310 --> 00:12:16,950
-Good!
-Good!

223
00:12:20,140 --> 00:12:23,380
The prince investigated military funds,

224
00:12:23,710 --> 00:12:27,020
devoted to the country
and the world's peace.

225
00:12:27,500 --> 00:12:30,690
He saved her when she was in danger.

226
00:12:31,190 --> 00:12:34,790
The story continued with
the princess's visit to the military camp.

227
00:12:34,410 --> 00:12:36,950
[Elegant Songs and Dances]

228
00:12:34,830 --> 00:12:36,230
At Hanyan Temple, a drama unfolded.

229
00:12:36,230 --> 00:12:37,230
Truly wonderful.

230
00:12:38,590 --> 00:12:41,850
The princess is well-matched
with the prince.

231
00:12:39,660 --> 00:12:41,920
[Elegant Songs and Dances]

232
00:12:42,310 --> 00:12:45,750
In a quiet courtyard, under moonlight,

233
00:12:46,230 --> 00:12:48,140
bound by a red string,
they build a home together.

234
00:12:48,140 --> 00:12:48,800
Tan.

235
00:12:51,110 --> 00:12:52,590
Why are you here?

236
00:12:52,620 --> 00:12:53,620
You're so far back.

237
00:12:53,620 --> 00:12:54,780
How can you see clearly?

238
00:12:54,780 --> 00:12:55,820
Let me tell you.

239
00:12:55,840 --> 00:12:56,620
After today,

240
00:12:56,620 --> 00:12:57,690
our storybook

241
00:12:57,710 --> 00:12:59,110
is bound to spread across the capital

242
00:12:59,110 --> 00:13:00,710
and become the most popular.

243
00:13:00,740 --> 00:13:04,020
-Good!
-Good!

244
00:13:04,020 --> 00:13:04,660
Good!

245
00:13:06,470 --> 00:13:09,650
[Ode to Peace and Prosperity]

246
00:13:17,580 --> 00:13:19,640
This is the right place.

247
00:13:22,060 --> 00:13:22,690
Wake up.

248
00:13:22,720 --> 00:13:23,790
Why are you all asleep?

249
00:13:23,790 --> 00:13:25,050
Get to work, all of you.

250
00:13:25,470 --> 00:13:26,270
Erbao!

251
00:13:30,190 --> 00:13:31,020
Master,

252
00:13:31,260 --> 00:13:32,020
you're here.

253
00:13:32,050 --> 00:13:33,050
What's going on?

254
00:13:33,070 --> 00:13:34,110
Usually, Wentao Pavilion

255
00:13:34,110 --> 00:13:35,250
is full of guests.

256
00:13:35,280 --> 00:13:36,120
How come there's not

257
00:13:36,120 --> 00:13:36,780
a single guest today?

258
00:13:36,780 --> 00:13:37,930
You haven't heard?

259
00:13:38,020 --> 00:13:39,660
The lady from the Duke of Chang's Mansion

260
00:13:39,660 --> 00:13:41,030
suddenly had inspiration

261
00:13:41,030 --> 00:13:41,970
and wrote

262
00:13:42,000 --> 00:13:43,470
a very interesting storybook.

263
00:13:43,470 --> 00:13:45,090
They've been performing it all day

264
00:13:45,090 --> 00:13:46,290
on South Yuhe Street.

265
00:13:46,490 --> 00:13:48,020
Everyone's chasing the novelty,

266
00:13:48,020 --> 00:13:49,030
so

267
00:13:49,190 --> 00:13:50,660
they all went there for it.

268
00:13:51,610 --> 00:13:52,440
Her?

269
00:13:52,830 --> 00:13:54,070
What kind of storybook could she write

270
00:13:54,070 --> 00:13:55,500
to compete with Wentao Pavilion?

271
00:13:55,500 --> 00:13:57,940
I don't know.

272
00:13:58,070 --> 00:13:59,270
Master, why don't you

273
00:13:59,830 --> 00:14:01,130
go take a look

274
00:14:01,230 --> 00:14:03,060
and pick up a thing or two?

275
00:14:05,900 --> 00:14:07,940
Erbao, here. Hold this fan.

276
00:14:08,230 --> 00:14:09,030
Hit yourself!

277
00:14:15,460 --> 00:14:16,720
Alright, give it to me.

278
00:14:16,870 --> 00:14:18,770
[Ode to Peace and Prosperity]

279
00:14:17,490 --> 00:14:18,990
Tell them all to go home and rest.

280
00:14:18,990 --> 00:14:20,650
We'll deduct two days' wages.

281
00:14:21,260 --> 00:14:22,170
